# MCP-AIWorker: Tokenizer Barrier Infrastructure

[![CI](https://github.com/ayato-labs/MCP-AIWorker/actions/workflows/ci.yml/badge.svg)](https://github.com/ayato-labs/MCP-AIWorker/actions/workflows/ci.yml)
[![License: MIT](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-yellow.svg)](https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT)
[![PRs Welcome](https://img.shields.io/badge/PRs-welcome-brightgreen.svg)](https://github.com/ayato-labs/MCP-AIWorker/pulls)

[日本語版はこちら (Japanese Version)](README_JA.md)

**MCP-AIWorker** is a high-performance **Tokenizer Barrier**—an MCP server designed to act as a cost-efficient middleware for any AI Agent system.

Whether you use Claude Code, Cursor, or custom agents, MCP-AIWorker intercepts token-heavy, mechanical tasks—such as drafting repetitive code, summarizing massive log outputs, and parsing web content—and delegates them to inexpensive, high-speed models (like Google Gemini Flash 3.1) or local LLMs. 

Your main "Architect" AI stays focused on high-level reasoning and design, while MCP-AIWorker drastically reduces your API token overhead.

---

## 🛡️ Why Use a Tokenizer Barrier?

Agents that perform file-wide analysis and compile-run-debug loops often waste the majority of your context window and API budget on repetitive typing and log processing. 

MCP-AIWorker optimizes this by implementing the **Architect-Worker Paradigm**:
*   **Drastic Cost Reduction**: Offloads structural coding, log analysis, and translation tasks to cost-effective model tiers.
*   **Reduced Context Bloat**: Keeps the Main AI's context clean by providing concise summaries instead of dumping raw, massive log or web files.
*   **Predictable Performance**: Rejects complex, non-deterministic internal QA loops. The Architect AI retains absolute control, ensuring the system remains fast and predictable.
*   **Platform Agnostic**: Being an MCP server, it can be integrated into **any** MCP-compliant client.

### Token Usage Tracking & Cost Observatory
MCP-AIWorker includes built-in telemetry to prove its value.
1. It automatically tracks token usage per tool execution in a local SQLite database.
2. View your real-time cost savings and token consumption metrics:
```bash
.venv\Scripts\python.exe scripts\show_dashboard.py
```

---

## 🏗️ Architecture

```
                 +------------------------+
                 |    Main AI Agent       |
                 |      (Architect)       |  <-- High-level Reasoning & Design
                 +-----------+------------+
                             |
                     MCP Tool Calls
                             v
                 +-----------+------------+
                 |      MCP-AIWorker      |  <-- Tokenizer Barrier
                 +-----------+------------+
                             |
             +---------------+---------------+
             |               |               |
             v               v               v
      +------------+   +------------+  +------------+
      |   Gemini   |   |   Ollama   |  |  Genspark  |  <-- Cheap / Local LLMs
      |   (API)    |   |  (Local)   |  | (Search)   |      for Heavy Typing & Logs
      +------------+   +------------+  +------------+
```

---

## 🚀 Quick Start (Windows)

### 1. Setup Environment
```bash
setup.bat
```

### 2. Configure `.env`
```env
AI_PROVIDER=gemini
GOOGLE_API_KEY=your-api-key-here
DRAFTING_MODEL=models/gemini-3.1-flash-lite
```

### 3. Start the Server
```bash
run.bat
```
The server will boot on `http://127.0.0.1:10300/mcp`.

---

## 🛠️ MCP Tools Exposed

| Tool | Purpose |
| :--- | :--- |
| `draft_code` | Localized, high-speed code drafting. |
| `find_and_draft_edit` | Directory-wide targeting and modification. |
| `execute_command` | Executes terminal commands; returns concise, AI-ready log summaries. |
| `fetch_and_summarize_url` | Summarizes web content without consuming excessive tokens. |
| `generate_unit_tests` | AAA-pattern unit test generation. |

---

## 📄 Core Philosophy (ADRs)

We build with strict architectural discipline. See our [ADRs](docs/ADR/) for detailed reasoning on why we intentionally **do not** implement complex features like Git conflict resolution or automated task routing. Our power lies in focus, not feature bloat.

